                                                      [{"description":"<div>Weâ€™re here to be your crypto guide with expert-built portfolios, in-depth resources, and a simple investing experience.</div>","entity_footer_disclosure":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":1,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"entity_original_content","labelTranslations":{},"name":"entity_original_content","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"hs_child_table_id":0,"hs_created_at":1697129913254,"hs_deleted_at":0,"hs_id":139925872435,"hs_is_edited":false,"hs_name":"Investing in the future with crypto","hs_path":"investing-in-future","hs_published_at":1728501899794,"hs_updated_at":1699903417858,"hs_updated_by_user_id":18663035,"meta_description":"Weâ€™re here to be your crypto guide with expert-built portfolios, in-depth resources, and a simple investing experience.","optional_footer_disclosures":[{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":2,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","labelTranslations":{},"name":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0}],"order":1,"playlist":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":5,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"Explainers","labelTranslations":{},"name":"Explainers","order":4,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"show_on_hub":1,"thumbnail":{"url":"https://www.betterment.com/hubfs/custom-video-thumbnails/thumbnail-pqineh0nwn-investing-in-the-future-with-crypto.png","altText":"","type":"image"},"title":"Investing in the future with crypto","transcript":"<p>Our goal is to be your guide on your crypto investing journey. For us at Betterment, we are taking a long-term approach and are building diversified portfolios of cryptocurrencies for investors to choose from. Crypto may be the first opportunity that all investors have had to participate in an asset class from its beginning. If you think about angel investing or investing in startups, it's often been limited to a few select investors, but with crypto, the investment opportunities are open to everybody.</p>\n<p>If you're comfortable with crypto, at Betterment, we recommend holding 5% or less of your investable assets in crypto alongside your other investments. It gives you a chance to invest in the future, while adding another element of diversification. As we live in an uncertain world, diversification can be an investor's best friend.</p>","updated_date":1665187200000,"wistia_id":"pqineh0nwn"},{"description":"<p>Find out the difference between DIY and expert-built portfolios.</p>\n<p> </p>","entity_footer_disclosure":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":1,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"entity_original_content","labelTranslations":{},"name":"entity_original_content","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"hs_child_table_id":0,"hs_created_at":1697129913266,"hs_deleted_at":0,"hs_id":139925872436,"hs_is_edited":false,"hs_name":"","hs_path":"how-to-invest-crypto","hs_published_at":1728501899794,"hs_updated_at":1699648519316,"hs_updated_by_user_id":18663035,"meta_description":"Find out the difference between DIY and expert-built portfolios.","optional_footer_disclosures":[{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":2,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","labelTranslations":{},"name":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0}],"order":2,"playlist":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":5,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"Explainers","labelTranslations":{},"name":"Explainers","order":4,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"show_on_hub":1,"thumbnail":{"url":"https://www.betterment.com/hubfs/custom-video-thumbnails/thumbnail-xkgegax73s-how-to-invest-in-crypto.png","altText":"","type":"image"},"title":"A better way to invest in crypto","transcript":"We boil this down into two categories, do-it-yourself crypto or DIY crypto and managed crypto portfolios. We recommend a managed crypto portfolio. It works like an ETF. Our experts build and manage portfolios on your behalf. Both options come with risk, but a managed crypto portfolio is an easy way to manage risk through diversification.","updated_date":1665187200000,"wistia_id":"xkgegax73s"},{"description":"<p>Crypto investing is complex. Weâ€™re trying to make it simpler.</p>","entity_footer_disclosure":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":1,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"entity_original_content","labelTranslations":{},"name":"entity_original_content","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"hs_child_table_id":0,"hs_created_at":1697129913278,"hs_deleted_at":0,"hs_id":139925872437,"hs_is_edited":false,"hs_name":"The fundamentals of crypto at Betterment","hs_path":"better-crypto-investing","hs_published_at":1728501899794,"hs_updated_at":1699903422475,"hs_updated_by_user_id":18663035,"meta_description":"Unlock the future with Betterment's crypto portfolios. Broadly diversified portfolios, direct ownership, and simplicity on one platform. Your guide to hassle-free crypto investing with Betterment.","optional_footer_disclosures":[{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":2,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","labelTranslations":{},"name":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0}],"order":3,"playlist":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":5,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"Explainers","labelTranslations":{},"name":"Explainers","order":4,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"show_on_hub":1,"thumbnail":{"url":"https://www.betterment.com/hubfs/custom-video-thumbnails/thumbnail-czkdhoqi9q-what-makes-betterments-approach-to-crypto-different.png","altText":"","type":"image"},"title":"The fundamentals of crypto at Betterment","transcript":"We're here for you, that's what sets us apart. We really strive to make sure that crypto fits into your long-term financial plan. Our key to doing that is through broadly diversified crypto portfolios that enable you to directly own a wide range of cryptocurrencies. Plus, we make it easy.\n\nNo need to manage digital wallets, just one simple platform. At the same time, we provide educational resources so you understand your investment. Our goal is to be your guide on your crypto investing journey.","updated_date":1665187200000,"wistia_id":"czkdhoqi9q"},{"description":"Learn why economic shifts aren't as dire as they sound and gain insights on smart investment moves during uncertain times.","entity_footer_disclosure":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":1,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"entity_original_content","labelTranslations":{},"name":"entity_original_content","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"hs_child_table_id":0,"hs_created_at":1697129913243,"hs_deleted_at":0,"hs_id":139925872434,"hs_is_edited":false,"hs_name":"How to approach market volatility","hs_path":"market-volatility-explainer","hs_published_at":1728501899794,"hs_updated_at":1699903424297,"hs_updated_by_user_id":18663035,"meta_description":"Learn why economic shifts aren't as dire as they sound and gain insights on smart investment moves during uncertain times.Stress less, invest wisely.","optional_footer_disclosures":[{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":2,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","labelTranslations":{},"name":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0}],"order":4,"playlist":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":5,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"Explainers","labelTranslations":{},"name":"Explainers","order":4,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"show_on_hub":1,"thumbnail":{"url":"https://www.betterment.com/hubfs/custom-video-thumbnails/thumbnail-q2bnj1fomj-market-volatility.png","altText":"","height":1620,"type":"image","width":3240},"title":"How to approach market volatility","transcript":"<p>Hey everyone! I'm Dan Egan, Director of Behavioral Finance here at Betterment. So you might have heard there's a lot going on: inflation going up, interest rates rising, commodity prices spiking, energy prices spiking, and housing affordability going down. A lot of this can seem really concerning and cause anxiety when you start thinking about how it might impact your portfolio.</p>\n<p>Let's take a step back and see why this might not be as dire as it sounds. First off, interest rates and inflation. Right now we've got low unemployment, but inflation is going up. So the Fed is doing exactly what you would expect, namely trying to cool the economy off a little bit, get inflation back down by increasing the risk free interest rate.</p>\n<p>That means savers will have higher interest rates in their cash savings accounts like Cash Reserve. But it would also mean that if you were looking to buy a house, you're going to have to pay a higher rate of interest on the mortgage. That's normal. The big question for first-time investors is, is now the right time</p>\n<p>It can feel scary to invest right after a market drawdown. It can also feel scary to invest after the market's been doing great for a while. Unfortunately, there's no easy, perfect time to start investing. Imagine paying the price to go to a concert and then not going.</p>\n<p>That's what it's like when you sell after a market drop and you're not there for the rally. Stress decisions are bad decisions. If you're looking at your portfolio and it's making you anxious or stressed, if you're thinking about it a lot, that's not a good place to be. So try and reset your relationship with how often you monitor your portfolio.</p>\n<p>You should only be looking at it if you're going to make a decision. One of the big concerns in the room that I want to talk about is inflation. Inflation eats away at your money over time. So if you're thinking about what to do with your money for six months or less.</p>\n<p>Don't let inflation influence your decision. On the other hand, if you're doing something longer term with your money, say, two years plus, that's when inflation can really start to erode the value of it. So you want to make sure wherever you're putting your money is going to be good for a long term return. Now, if you are strongly motivated to do something during a market drop, there's actually a lot of smart things you can do.</p>\n<p>Fund your safety net to a healthy level. Nothing will help you stress less about market drops than knowing you've created an emergency fund for exactly moments like this. Don't go all or nothing in or out. Reduce your stock allocation a little bit, say 10% to 15% Something to give yourself a little bit of relaxation, but not getting out entirely.</p>\n<p>Market drops are a great opportunity to check and see if you should rebalance back into stocks and riskier assets after they've fallen. Another thing you can do is use this as a catalyst to check in on your financial plans and timelines. Start with your goals. Is there anything you need to adjust?</p>\n<p>Are your priorities reflected in how you're saving and investing? One way to make lemonade out of lemons during a market drop, check for tax loss harvesting opportunities. Or let us do it for you.</p>","updated_date":1655337600000,"wistia_id":"q2bnj1fomj"},{"description":"In this episode of \"How I Money,\" we hear how a college grad turned living with her parents into a strategic financial move. Learn about housing costs, retirement investing, and the importance of financial literacy.","entity_footer_disclosure":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":1,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"entity_original_content","labelTranslations":{},"name":"entity_original_content","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"hs_child_table_id":0,"hs_created_at":1697129913291,"hs_deleted_at":0,"hs_id":139925872438,"hs_is_edited":false,"hs_name":"How I Money: Surabhi","hs_path":"how-i-money-surabhi","hs_published_at":1728501899794,"hs_updated_at":1699903426356,"hs_updated_by_user_id":18663035,"meta_description":"In this episode of \"How I Money,\" we hear how a college grad turned living with her parents into a strategic financial move. Learn about housing costs, retirement investing, and the importance of financial literacy.","optional_footer_disclosures":[{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":2,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","labelTranslations":{},"name":"optional_b4c_betterment_llc","order":0,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0}],"order":5,"playlist":{"createdAt":null,"createdByUserId":0,"id":5,"isHubspotDefined":false,"label":"Explainers","labelTranslations":{},"name":"Explainers","order":4,"type":"option","updatedAt":null,"updatedByUserId":0},"show_on_hub":1,"thumbnail":{"url":"https://www.betterment.com/hubfs/custom-video-thumbnails/thumbnail-7luk54cc5n-how-i-money-surabhi.png","altText":"","type":"image"},"title":"How I Money: Surabhi","transcript":"<p>My name is Surabhi. I am 23, and I'm a software engineer.</p>\n<p>[WHAT'S YOUR EARLIEST MEMORY OF MONEY?]</p>\n<p>I remember always being really excited to get more money, to get more tokens at Chuck E. Cheese. I used to have this tub of tickets. I used to be obsessed with--I still am kind of--stuffed animals. </p>\n<p>[WHAT MOTIVATES YOU TO SAVE?]</p>\n<p>The thought of not working someday if I'm being brutally honest.</p>\n<p>A lot of people my age have the mindset that OK, I graduated and now you're making paychecks, and it's really nice and you have this influx of money. And so what do people do when they get that? They want to expand their lifestyle. I've always thought about it kind of in the inverse. If I set a really good foundation, it will allow me to have more freedom in the future.</p>\n<p>[DO YOU TALK MONEY WITH FRIENDS?]</p>\n<p>Some friends yes some friends no. Everybody's relationship with money is so different, and can sometimes be such a sensitive topic. Now also, it's easier to talk to an unbiased party. I had a mentor in college who I still talk to. He was kind of the one who coached me into investing, and then now when it comes to salary and just talking about work and promotions and things like that, I always go to him. It's important to find somebody like that in your life.</p>\n<p>[WHAT'S THE BEST MONEY YOU'VE EVER SPENT?]</p>\n<p>Honestly, this water bottle. OK. This is a shameless promotion for this water bottle. It has literally changed my life.</p>\n<p>But I think a more general answer is I feel like any trip I go on. I went to Peru with my friends, and we did these crazy hiking excursions and ate the best food and it was so fun and that's like one of my best memories from college, and I love that. So that was some of the best money I've spent.</p>","updated_date":1676419200000,"wistia_id":"7luk54cc5n"}]
